rComments: unexpected hard questions on final exams. I don't think we are able to do those with the contents that we learned in this course. Too much computation.

He is a ok instructor, but his test is way too hard than needed, and even if you understand everything from the lecture but could not do all the math very quick, you won't get a good grade in this course. Also, the content of this course is very practical, so it is weird that this course doesn't have any assignment.

Although the test problems are difficult, at least they are fair to all the students. He refuses to use past test problems so that the students going to private tutoring services can not get any advantage. This brings complaints from students replying on tutoring services. His homework and review problems are helpful.

Although he has no passion of teaching(better than average ut prof ), he gives students fair marks. His lecture size are around 200ish, but only 40-50 go to the lecture. He still curve the average to b-. His gives useful self studying homework and Final review questions. If you skip class or don't do homework, how could you get a good grade?

has no passion of teaching and expects students to be the masters of all the materials. No application or R practice at all where the course content is meant to be practical. Hardest final you can get. Tries to trick students to lower the avg.
He gives super hard midterms and finals with very low averages. His lectures and practice problems were useless and didn't prepare for these. Avoid him.
the questions of tests are very similar to those questions he posted in BB and the lecture notes.
Boring lectures, he just copies his notes onto the blackboard without much explaining anything.
